data.name: instructions.Text
data.value:
Your party of heroes is traveling along the Oregon Trail because ... just because they want to. However, your heroes encounter some enemies along the way. It is your job to make sure that you get rid of these enemies as your party approaches their destination in Oregon.
Your party will encounter 1-3 enemies for each round. There will be three rounds. Those enemies could either be ogres, bandits, or dragons. Each entity will take a turn peforming either an attack, defense, or special move. For your heroes, it is your choice to perform one of these actions. Pressing the attack button will grant you the ability to attack any one of the enemies. Pressing the defense button will create a "shield" for the hero. If an enemy attacks that hero, then hit points will decrease. Pressing the special move button will let the hero use their special move (which is a surprise). However, these moves cost 25 skill points.
Each hero starts off with 100 health points and 100 skill points. If all heros have 0 health points, then the game is over. If all enemies have 0 health points, then the game moves on to the next round, and the heros' health points and skill points are reset. If your party defeats all enemies for all three rounds, then yay! You won the game.

data.name: charGuide.Text
data.value:
The Warrior does physical damage, has high physical defense, and is weak to magic. The Mage does magic damage, has low physical defense, and is strong against magic. The Cleric can heal other heroes, is weak in attacks, and has a fair defense against both physical and magical attacks. When defending, they can often absorb an enemy's energy from their attack and convert that into heatlh points.
The Bandit is just a weak enemy. The Ogre is a slow yet powerful guy who is weak to magic but strong against physical attacks. The Dragon is the strongest enemy; be careful! It can breathe fire and swipe the heroes off their feet.
When defending, your hero can occasionally absorb energy from the enemy's attack and gain health from that. Be wise with your skill points! Use your special moves carefully because that will decrease your hero's skill points. If there is no more skill points, then you cannot perform a special move.
Points System: Defeating a: Bandit = 100 Ogre = 250 Dragon = 500 Winning a Round = 1000 Winning a Game = 5000
